class Solution {
    public int kthFactor(int n, int k) {
        int count = 0;
        for (int i = 1; i <= Math.sqrt(n); i++) {
            if (n % i == 0) {
                count++;
                if (count == k) return i;
                if (i * i != n) {
                    if (count + 1 == k) return n / i;
                    count++;
                }
            }
        }
        return -1;
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(sqrt(n))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Iterating up to sqrt(n) and checking for factors, returning the kth factor or its corresponding pair factor if it exists, otherwise returning -1.
